codeSystems.name: AdministrativeGender
codeSystems.title: AdministrativeGender
codeSystems.description: The gender of a person used for administrative purposes.

codeSystems.name: BundleType
codeSystems.title: BundleType
codeSystems.description: Indicates the purpose of a bundle - how it is intended to be used.

codeSystems.name: PracticeSettingCodeValueSet
codeSystems.title: Practice Setting Code Value Set
codeSystems.description: This is the code representing the clinical specialty of the clinician or provider who interacted with, treated, or provided a service to/for the patient. The value set used for clinical specialty has been limited by HITSP to the value set reproduced from HITSP C80 Table 2-149 Clinical Specialty Value Set Definition.

codeSystems.name: CommonTags
codeSystems.title: Common Tags
codeSystems.description: Common Tag Codes defined by FHIR project

codeSystems.name: DaysOfWeek
codeSystems.title: DaysOfWeek
codeSystems.description: The days of the week.

codeSystems.name: HTTPVerb
codeSystems.title: HTTPVerb
codeSystems.description: HTTP verbs (in the HTTP command line). See [HTTP rfc](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231) for details.

codeSystems.name: Identifier Type Codes
codeSystems.title: IdentifierType
codeSystems.description: A coded type for an identifier that can be used to determine which identifier to use for a specific purpose.

codeSystems.name: IdentifierUse
codeSystems.title: IdentifierUse
codeSystems.description: Identifies the purpose for this identifier, if known .

codeSystems.name: CommonLanguages
codeSystems.title: Common Languages
codeSystems.description: This value set includes common codes from BCP-47 (http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47)

codeSystems.name: LinkType
codeSystems.title: LinkType
codeSystems.description: The type of link between this patient resource and another patient resource.

codeSystems.name: Marital Status Codes
codeSystems.title: MaritalStatus
codeSystems.description: This value set defines the set of codes that can be used to indicate the marital status of a person.

codeSystems.name: Mime Types
codeSystems.title: MimeType
codeSystems.description: This value set includes all possible codes from BCP-13 (http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp13)

codeSystems.name: PatientContactRelationship
codeSystems.title: Patient Contact Relationship
codeSystems.description: The nature of the relationship between the patient and the contact person.

codeSystems.name: ProcedurePerformerRoleCodes
codeSystems.title: Procedure Performer Role Codes
codeSystems.description: This example value set defines the set of codes that can be used to indicate a role of a procedure performer.

codeSystems.name: PractitionerRole
codeSystems.title: Practitioner role
codeSystems.description: This example value set defines a set of codes that can be used to indicate the role of a Practitioner.

codeSystems.name: QuestionnaireAnswerCodes
codeSystems.title: Questionnaire Answer Codes
codeSystems.description: Example list of codes for answers to questions. (Not complete or necessarily appropriate.)

codeSystems.name: QuestionnaireResponseStatus
codeSystems.title: QuestionnaireResponseStatus
codeSystems.description: Lifecycle status of the questionnaire response.

codeSystems.name: RequestPriority
codeSystems.title: Request priority
codeSystems.description: The clinical priority of a diagnostic order.

codeSystems.name: ResourceType
codeSystems.title: ResourceType
codeSystems.description: One of the resource types defined as part of this version of FHIR.

codeSystems.name: SearchEntryMode
codeSystems.title: SearchEntryMode
codeSystems.description: Why an entry is in the result set - whether it's included as a match or because of an _include requirement, or to convey information or warning information about the search process.

codeSystems.name: All Security Labels
codeSystems.title: SecurityLabels
codeSystems.description: A single value set for all security labels defined by FHIR.

codeSystems.name: SignatureTypeCodes
codeSystems.title: Signature Type Codes
codeSystems.description: The Digital Signature Purposes, an indication of the reason an entity signs a document. This is included in the signed information and can be used when determining accountability for various actions concerning the document. Examples include: author, transcriptionist/recorder, and witness.

codeSystems.name: TaskIntent
codeSystems.title: TaskIntent
codeSystems.description: Distinguishes whether the task is a proposal, plan or full order.

codeSystems.name: USCoreDocumentReferenceType
codeSystems.title: US Core DocumentReference Type
codeSystems.description: The US Core DocumentReference Type Value Set includes all LOINC values whose SCALE is "Doc" in the LOINC database and the HL7 v3 Code System NullFlavor concept 'unknown'

codeSystems.name: CDexPOUCodes
codeSystems.title: CDex Purpose of Use Value Set
codeSystems.description: The set of purpose of use (POU) codes for requesting data. This code set is composed of [FHIR core Purpose of Use security labels](http://hl7.org/fhir/security-labels.html#core) and additional codes defined by this Guide.

codeSystems.name: CDexClaimUseCodes
codeSystems.title: CDex Claim Use Value Set
codeSystems.description: The purpose of a Claim resource and the reason for attachments. It includes the codes "preauthorization" and "claim".

codeSystems.name: CDexDataRequestTaskCode
codeSystems.title: CDex Data Request Task Code Value Set
codeSystems.description: Codes used to identify the type of data request. It includes the codes “data-request-query”, “data-request-code”, and “data-request-questionnaire”.

codeSystems.name: CDexIdentifierTypes
codeSystems.title: CDex Identifier Types Value Set
codeSystems.description: Identifier types for providers and organizations. It includes the codes “TAX” and “NPI”.

codeSystems.name: CDexLOINCAttachmentCodesValueSet
codeSystems.title: CDex LOINC Attachment Codes Value Set
codeSystems.description: This value set includes LOINC terms that can be sent by a payer as part of an HL7 attachment request for additional information. It has been curated by the HL7 Payer/Provider Information Exchange (PIE) Work Group.  More information about using LOINC in HIPAA attachments and the source of this value set can be found at [LOINC Attahments](https://loinc.org/attachments/).

codeSystems.name: CDexPWK01AttachmentReportTypeCodeValueSet
codeSystems.title: CDex PWK01 Attachment Report Type Code Value Set
codeSystems.description:
In addition to using LOINC attachment codes, a payer may request for additional information from the provider to support a prior authorization request using X12's PWK01 Attachment Report Type Code.

Note that the PWK01 codes will not be published in due to X12 IP restrictions.

codeSystems.name: CDexWorkQueueCodes
codeSystems.title: CDex Work Queue Value Set
codeSystems.description: The set work queue tags that the provider may use in their workflow to process requests. This code set is composed of codes defined by this Guide.

codeSystems.name: HRexTaskStatus
codeSystems.title: HRex Task Status ValueSet
codeSystems.description: The set of task codes allowed for use in HRex data request tasks

codeSystems.name: PASTaskCodes
codeSystems.title: PAS Task Codes
codeSystems.description: The code for the task that is request additional information.
